# vibe's own content-guard allowlist (task_019).
#
# One ERE regex per line; `#` comments and blank lines ignored; case-
# sensitive. A finding is suppressed iff its WHOLE FLAGGED LINE matches
# (grep -E) an entry below. See devcontainer/claude-md/content-guard.md.
#
# Scope: doc/fragment illustrative literals ONLY — the examples below teach
# the guard's own PII categories in devcontainer/claude-md/project-hygiene.md,
# ssh-discipline.md, and content-guard.md. None of these are real leaked
# credentials or a live host this repo depends on.

# Hygiene-doc example PII.
/Users/martin/
/Users/<your-name>/
/Users/<name>/
mcomz\.local
pi02\.local
192\.168\.0\.96

# Claude Code's own runtime-config filename (.claude/settings.local.json,
# referenced throughout project-hygiene.md) — a false positive against the
# `.local` mDNS-hostname rule, not a hostname at all.
settings\.local\.json

# SECURITY.md maintainer contact link.
github\.com/Aqueum

# Pre-existing tracked-doc literals (CHANGELOG.md / MANUAL-TESTS.md) — none
# real secrets or live hosts this repo depends on; all predate this guard.
# CHANGELOG prose "...opus->ask-before-Fable-on-locked-spec" trips the
# `sk-` OpenAI-key rule as a false positive ("a" + "sk-before-...").
ask-before-Fable-on-locked-spec
# CHANGELOG prose naming Docker Desktop's observed host-gateway IP.
192\.168\.65\.254
# MANUAL-TESTS git-config example address.
test@example\.com
# MANUAL-TESTS ZOTERO_API_KEY fixture value (a documented placeholder, not a
# real key — matches the secret-named-assignment rule).
TESTKEY0001testkey0002zz

# task_023 path-warn entries (WARN-tier only — a real secret in either path
# still BLOCKs; see devcontainer/claude-md/content-guard.md). Harness prose
# under .vs/ and smoke-test.py's runtime fixtures deliberately discuss/hold
# WARN-class example literals (RFC1918 IPs, example emails, .local
# hostnames) as part of teaching or exercising the guard's own rules — not
# real leaked PII.
path-warn:.vs/*
path-warn:smoke-test.py
